<h1 class='mt-4 mb-8 uppercase opacity-25 text-lg text-center'>
  Welcome
</h1>

<div class="font-semibold">
  <h1>
    Welcome to EmberConf 2019!
  </h1>

  <div class="text-3xl mt-12">
    <div>
      1. Open terminal
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      2. Clone this git repository:
    </div>
    <p><span class="font-semibold bg-grey-light py-1 px-2 rounded">git clone git@github.com:embermap/emberconf2019-robust-data-fetching.git</span></p>

    <div class="mt-6">
      3. Move into the directory: <span class="font-semibold bg-grey-light py-1 px-2 rounded">cd emberconf2019-robust-data-fetching</span>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      4. Run NPM install: <span class="font-semibold bg-grey-light py-1 px-2 rounded">npm install</span> (You might get some warnings, thats ok!)
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      5. Serve the app <span class="font-semibold bg-grey-light py-1 px-2 rounded">npx ember s</span>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      6. Visit {{#link-to "1" class="text-blue underline"}}http://localhost:4200{{/link-to}}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      7. If you can see this screen, you're all set!
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
